verbs.description: oversweep (third-person singular simple present oversweeps, present participle oversweeping, simple past and past participle overswept)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To sweep over; to cover by sweeping.
examples: Ah, sure no tasteful nook would be without themAnd let a lush laburnum oversweep them,And let long grass grow round the roots to keep themMoist, cool and green; and shade the violetsThat they may bind the moss in leafy nets.
